  toponymy the word darjeeling has evolved from the sanskrit , " durjaya linga " , means " shiva of invincible prowess , who rules the himalayas . " it is also believed that the name darjeeling also comes from the tibetan word dorje , meaning the thunderbolt sceptre of the hindu deity indra , and ling , a place or land .

tea time : darjeeling tea is grown in darjeeling , india , in the foothills of these mountains

the himalayas